The original MS. of Plautus belonged probably to the 5th century, and if it were preserved entire at the present day, would be an authority of pai-amount importance upon the text of the whole of Plautus ; but in the 9th century it was taken to pieces‚ and ruthlessly washed and scraped3 upon the parchment thus prepared a copy of the Vulgate was made. The original writing is therefore exceed- ingly hard to decipher, and about two-thirds of the leaves are entirely lost.
